AMR Corp's American Airlines said it isprepared to shift a total of 1,010 flights and add more than 33hours a day in flying time to assist the process of reducingflight delays in the nation's air transport system.    American said it proposes to make the changes on June 15 atits two major conecting hubs, Dallas/Fort Worth and Chicago,which have been the focal points for wide-ranging scheduleexperiments by the airline over the past several weeks. Reuter&#3;